<HEADLINE>
PRESIDENT TO ATTEND SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT CONFERENCE
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May 24 (CNA) 05/24/07  11:57:28 (By Y.F. Low)
</P>
<P>
President Chen Shui-bian is scheduled to attend an international
conference on sustainable development slated for May 26 in
Kaohsiung and present the first "Life Sustainability" prizes to
11 recipients, organizers said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The  International  Conference  on Cultural  Diversity  and
Sustainable Development is being co-organized by the Ricci
Institute, the MOFA, the Council for Cultural Affairs (CCA) and
the Kaohsiung City Government.
</P>
<P>
Designed as a dialogue between Taiwan and Europe, the conference
will discuss the influence of European economic and environmental
protection policies on Taiwan, sustainable development and the
future of humankind, as well as global governance and the
question of how culture transcend politics, according to
officials at the Ricci Institute.
</P>
<P>
European participants in the conference will include Michel
Camdessus, chairman of the World Panel on Water Infrastructure
Financing; Dominique David, executive vice-president of the
Institut Francais des Relations Internationales; European
Economic and Trade Office  Director  Guy  Ledoux;  and  French
Senator  Joelle Garriaud-Maylam, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
The participants from Taiwan will include Kaohsiung Mayor Chen
Chu, Deputy Minister of Foreign Affairs Yang Tzu-pao, National
Cultural Association Secretary-General Tchen Yu-chiou, CCA Vice
Chairman Wu Ching-fa, writer Lu Ping, National Sun Yat-Sen
University President Chang Chung-cheng, National Pingtung
University of Science and Technology President Guu Yuan-kuang,
and Wenzao Ursuline College of Languages President Bosco Wen-ruey
Lee, they said.
</P>
